structure.unit: COUNTIES, CITIES, AND OTHER LOCAL UNITS
SHERIFFS, CONSTABLES, AND COUNTY POLICE FORCE

law.text: No constable shall return on any process that the defendant is not found, unless he has actually been to the defendant's residence and has not found him, if the defendant is a resident of the county.
law.history: Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 437.
